	<div class="logoContainer"><div class="logo"><a href="index.html"><img src="images/logo.png" width=90px></img></a></div></div>
	<div class="content">
		
			<h1>Graphical representation of data using JavaScript and HTML5</h1>
			<br>By <a class="author" href="https://twitter.com/Sudarshan8870" target="_blank">Sudarshan Sonowal</a> <span class="postDate">(May 13, 2015)</span>
			<p>
			<div class="codeArea">
			<code>
				&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br>
				&lt;html&gt;<br>
				&lt;head&gt;<br>
				&lt;title&gt;Pie Chart&lt;/title&gt;<br>
				&lt;/head&gt;<br>
				&lt;body&gt;<br><br>
				&lt;canvas id="myCanvas" width="600" height="500" style="background-color:lightgray;"&gt; &lt;/canvas&gt;<br><br>
				&lt;script&gt;<br><br>
				
				 //x position of the bars <br>
				 var x = 0; <br><br>
				 
				 //y position of the bars<br>
				 var y; <br><br>

				 var total = 0;<br>
			
				 var canvas= document.getElementById('myCanvas');
				 var context = canvas.getContext('2d');<br><br>
			
				  //array storing values to generate the bar chart <br>
				 var values = [180, 40, 400, 140, 67];<br><br>

				 for (var i = 0; i < values.length; i++){<br>
					&nbsp total += values[i];<br>
				 }<br><br>
			
				 for (var i = 0; i < values.length - 1; i++){ <br><br>
			
					&nbsp//aligning the bottom position of the bars<br>
					&nbsp y = 500 - values[i]; <br><br>
					&nbsp context.moveTo(x,y);<br>
					&nbsp x+= 100;<br>
					&nbsp y = 500 - values[i+1];<br>
					&nbsp context.lineTo(x,y);<br>
					&nbsp context.stroke();<br>
				}<br><br>
	
				&lt;/script&gt;<br><br>
			    &lt;/body&gt;<br>
				&lt;/html&gt;
			</code>
			</p>
		</div>
		<p><a class="demo" href="graphical_representation_of_data_using_javascript_and_html5_demo.html" target="_blank">Demo</a></p>
